# RTV Mod Checker

CLI tool to review Road to Vostok mods from newest to oldest and write one analysis folder per mod-version under `Mod-Checker/Analyses`.

## Install

```bash
cd Mod-Checker
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .
```

## Usage

Run newest-first scans:

```bash
mod-checker scan --source roadtovostok --limit 50
```

Useful flags:

- `--batch-size 1`: iterative mode (default), one mod per run
- `--dry-run`: build queue only
- `--force`: re-scan already reviewed versions
- `--only-mod-id <id>`: targeted scan
- `--since 2026-04-01T00:00:00`: ignore older uploads
- `--all`: traverse all listing pages (still respects `--batch-size`)
- `--base-url https://modworkshop.net/g/road-to-vostok`: override source URL

Scan exactly the next unscanned mod-version:

```bash
mod-checker scannext
mod-checker scannext --all
```

Scan all remaining unscanned mods one-by-one with progress bar:

```bash
mod-checker scannremaining --all
```

This command writes each analysis result immediately after each mod is scanned, so interruptions do not lose completed work.

List unscanned candidates (no scanning):

```bash
mod-checker candidates --limit 100 --format text
mod-checker candidates --all --format csv --output Analyses/reports/next-candidates.csv
```

## Outputs

Created per mod-version:

- `Mod-Checker/Analyses/<ModID>-<ModName>-<ModVersion>/metadata.json`
- `Mod-Checker/Analyses/<ModID>-<ModName>-<ModVersion>/scan-results.json`
- `Mod-Checker/Analyses/<ModID>-<ModName>-<ModVersion>/scan-summary.md`
- `Mod-Checker/Analyses/<ModID>-<ModName>-<ModVersion>/artifacts/*`

Run-level index:

- `Mod-Checker/Analyses/index.jsonl`

## Rule Coverage

The engine checks for:

- path traversal and symlink-like entries
- executable/script payloads in archives
- suspicious extensions and magic-byte mismatches
- PowerShell and process execution patterns
- network and obfuscation indicators
- suspicious update/download endpoints

## Safety Model

- Scanner performs static analysis only.
- Downloaded archives are never executed.
- Archive contents are read directly from the zip stream; files are not extracted to executable locations.

## Scheduling

Example cron (every hour):

```cron
0 * * * * cd /home/tq/CodeProjects/RTV-Mod-Checker/Mod-Checker && /home/tq/CodeProjects/RTV-Mod-Checker/Mod-Checker/.venv/bin/mod-checker scan --source roadtovostok --limit 100 >> /tmp/rtv-mod-checker.log 2>&1
```

